Date: 18/12/1895
Source: Colonist (Nelson)
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: I now have to refer to insects, or rather to one that I met with - the great Alpine Weta - whose bite is perhaps more dangerous than that of any other insect found in the forest .. It will be exhibited before the Natural History Society, Wellington, and named 'Deinacrida Broughi.'"
