Date: 0/0/1935
Source: NZ Alpine Journal
Author:
Vol / Page: 6/22/172
Edition:
Quote: The scientific name of the insect is <i>P. montanus.</i> It appears to be variously referred to as `Mount Cook Flea', `Jumping Spider' etc., but as the insect is allied to the weta, a more correct name would be <i>Alpine Weta. </i>
Notes:  (Dumbleton)
